1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:34,700
Here I come!

3
00:02:34,700 --> 00:02:37,070
Gum-Gum...

4
00:02:37,070 --> 00:02:38,860
Pistol!

5
00:02:43,640 --> 00:02:45,310
Now tell me...

6
00:02:46,050 --> 00:02:48,780
What are you even doing?!

7
00:02:48,780 --> 00:02:50,150
One point!

8
00:02:56,120 --> 00:02:58,260
I mean, seriously...

9
00:02:58,260 --> 00:03:01,720
what good are your powers anyway?

10
00:02:58,590 --> 00:03:06,030
Oath of Brotherhood

11
00:03:01,720 --> 00:03:07,230
Dammit! It's not working! I was so close, too!

12
00:03:07,230 --> 00:03:08,800
One more time!

13
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:12,500
No! The rule is only 100
matches per person a day.

14
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:13,540
Not till tomorrow.

15
00:03:13,540 --> 00:03:17,710
Luffy lost 50 times to Ace and me.

16
00:03:17,710 --> 00:03:21,280
Me versus Ace: 24 to 26.

17
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:24,120
I lost by 2. Dammit!

18
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:28,390
You guys...! When I'm ten,
I'll beat you both up!

19
00:03:28,390 --> 00:03:33,130
We'll be thirteen by then. Let's go find dinner.

20
00:03:40,940 --> 00:03:42,970
Alright, crocodile it is.

21
00:03:42,970 --> 00:03:45,300
Crocodile meat is so good!

22
00:03:45,300 --> 00:03:48,340
Luffy, don't get eaten this time.

23
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:51,540
You were only okay because
it swallowed you whole.

24
00:03:52,850 --> 00:03:56,520
Wait here, Luffy. Since you
can't swim, you'll slow us d–

25
00:03:56,980 --> 00:03:58,820
Crocodile meat!

26
00:03:58,820 --> 00:03:59,450
– What?!
– What?!

27
00:03:59,450 --> 00:04:01,440
I said to wait here!

28
00:04:09,880 --> 00:04:15,400
The harsh environment of Mt. Colubo
trained them day by day.

29
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:19,220
To the north of the mountain...

30
00:04:20,310 --> 00:04:24,310
is Gray Terminal, the final stop for
anything shrugged off by society.

31
00:04:25,410 --> 00:04:27,410
And just north of that place...

32
00:04:28,410 --> 00:04:33,120
stands a city enclosed by
an impenetrable wall made of solid stone.

33
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:41,690
The Great Gate is the city's only entrance...

34
00:04:41,690 --> 00:04:48,030
and twice a day, mountains of junk
from all over the country pass through it.

35
00:04:49,570 --> 00:04:51,540
Oh, here it comes!

36
00:04:51,540 --> 00:04:52,610
Let's go!

37
00:04:52,610 --> 00:04:54,040
It's treasure hunting time!

38
00:04:54,040 --> 00:05:00,710
Denizens of Gray Terminal occasionally
visit the city to sell their salvaged goods.

39
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:08,490
Hey, wait! What's in the package?

40
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:13,760
It's crocodile hide. I'm here to sell it.

41
00:05:13,760 --> 00:05:14,390
Crocodile?

42
00:05:17,530 --> 00:05:18,830
G-Go ahead!

43
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:25,900
Through the Great Gate is a boulevard
where passersby come cleanly into view,

44
00:05:25,900 --> 00:05:27,610
and beyond that lies Edge Town.

45
00:05:33,810 --> 00:05:38,720
Edge Town: a place that attracts
the thugs and gangsters of the city.

46
00:05:44,890 --> 00:05:48,630
Hold it, fella! We'll take that
package off your hands!

47
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:54,870
Hey, cat got your tongue?!

48
00:05:54,870 --> 00:05:56,370
Shut up, punk.

49
00:05:56,370 --> 00:05:56,870
What?!

50
00:06:00,940 --> 00:06:01,840
Y-You little...

51
00:06:01,840 --> 00:06:04,180
When you mug somebody...

52
00:06:06,510 --> 00:06:08,550
choose your mark wisely!

53
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:12,380
These guys... They're...

54
00:06:13,390 --> 00:06:14,550
Let's do this!

55
00:06:14,550 --> 00:06:15,890
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

56
00:06:33,240 --> 00:06:38,210
In the center of this enclosed city
is another towering stone wall.

57
00:06:38,210 --> 00:06:44,150
The wall surrounds High Town, the upper class
residential area for royalty and nobles.

58
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:50,190
This country is known as the Goa Kingdom.

59
00:06:50,190 --> 00:06:55,430
Its streets are spotless, and it is said to be
the most beautiful country in the East Blue.

60
00:06:58,560 --> 00:07:00,870
Windmill Village, where Luffy was born...

61
00:07:01,300 --> 00:07:05,970
is a forgotten backwater town,
though it is technically part of the kingdom.

62
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:12,310
Midtown

63
00:07:15,510 --> 00:07:18,220
Here are three bowls of ramen!
Sorry to keep you waiting!

64
00:07:18,520 --> 00:07:20,090
Enjoy your meal!

65
00:07:21,990 --> 00:07:23,820
So this is ramen?!

66
00:07:23,820 --> 00:07:25,420
It looks good!

67
00:07:27,430 --> 00:07:28,890
Well, eat up!

68
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:32,260
So good!

69
00:07:34,200 --> 00:07:35,930
Yeah, it is good!

70
00:07:39,870 --> 00:07:40,940
More pl–

71
00:07:42,870 --> 00:07:46,910
I'd like to order three more bowls of ramen!

72
00:07:46,910 --> 00:07:48,780
Yes, sir! Here they are!

73
00:07:48,780 --> 00:07:49,880
Pardon the intrusion!

74
00:07:58,360 --> 00:08:00,090
M-Manager!

75
00:08:00,090 --> 00:08:01,700
Are you sure?!

76
00:08:03,130 --> 00:08:05,260
Sir, we need to talk!

77
00:08:05,260 --> 00:08:06,700
Damn, they found out!

78
00:08:06,700 --> 00:08:07,990
Let's bail!

79
00:08:08,900 --> 00:08:10,670
They didn't pay!

80
00:08:10,670 --> 00:08:12,840
Somebody catch them!

81
00:08:12,840 --> 00:08:15,770
Ah! Ramen is so good!

82
00:08:15,770 --> 00:08:17,140
Told you so!

83
00:08:17,940 --> 00:08:19,380
Catch them?!

84
00:08:19,380 --> 00:08:20,910
But they're just kids!

85
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:29,190
I-It's those pesky brats again!
How the hell did they get in there?!

86
00:08:29,190 --> 00:08:34,560
Don't let them get away!
Somebody catch those three!

87
00:08:35,760 --> 00:08:39,030
I can't believe they jumped out of the window!

88
00:08:39,030 --> 00:08:41,830
This is the fourth floor!

89
00:08:41,830 --> 00:08:46,040
We're out twenty-six bowls
of ramen and a window!

90
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:50,040
M-Manager! They left a note!

91
00:08:54,030 --> 00:08:56,240
"Treasure tab"?!

92
00:09:02,550 --> 00:09:04,190
Sabo?

93
00:09:04,190 --> 00:09:06,260
That is Sabo! Please wait!

94
00:09:07,060 --> 00:09:09,030
You're alive!

95
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:11,360
Come back home!

96
00:09:12,730 --> 00:09:15,470
Hey, Sabo! He's calling you!

97
00:09:15,470 --> 00:09:16,230
Who's that?

98
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:19,940
He must think I'm someone else. Let's go!

99
00:09:22,240 --> 00:09:24,200
W-Wait right there!

100
00:09:35,350 --> 00:09:36,760
Sabo...

101
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:41,530
"We shall hereby visit
your country this spring"?

102
00:09:41,530 --> 00:09:45,500
Dogra! Magra! Where's this “Goa” place?!

103
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:52,870
M-Mt. Colubo, Gray Terminal, and Windmill Village
are all technically part of the Kingdom of Goa.

104
00:09:52,870 --> 00:09:54,440
That's what I thought.

105
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:56,480
Take it easy, Boss.

106
00:09:56,480 --> 00:10:01,980
It's rare to see you reading a newspaper.
Hell must be freezing over.

107
00:10:01,980 --> 00:10:03,820
Ouch!

108
00:10:03,820 --> 00:10:06,750
Somebody's gonna visit the kingdom?!

109
00:10:06,750 --> 00:10:10,290
It's making the headlines...

110
00:10:11,020 --> 00:10:14,190
What's going on here?
Are they that big a deal?

111
00:10:14,860 --> 00:10:17,200
These Celestial Dragons...?

