216
00:10:28,010 --> 00:10:30,440
What?! I'm not hiding anything!

217
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:34,110
Oh, you're not?

218
00:10:34,880 --> 00:10:37,950
Yes, you are! Tell us, Sabo!

219
00:10:39,220 --> 00:10:42,650
We can't have secrets between us!

220
00:10:44,090 --> 00:10:45,160
– Tell us!
– Tell us!

221
00:10:49,060 --> 00:10:51,730
Like I said, I'm not hiding...

222
00:10:51,730 --> 00:10:54,830
I'll beat the crap outta you
if you don't tell us, you jerk!

223
00:10:56,500 --> 00:10:58,700
Alright... Alright, I'll tell you!

224
00:11:01,040 --> 00:11:02,610
What?!

225
00:11:02,610 --> 00:11:04,410
The son of a noble?!

226
00:11:06,340 --> 00:11:07,610
– Who is?
– Who is?

227
00:11:07,610 --> 00:11:08,510
I am!

228
00:11:11,250 --> 00:11:12,150
– So?
– So?

229
00:11:12,150 --> 00:11:14,390
"So," you guys asked!

230
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:21,590
The truth is, both of my parents are alive.

231
00:11:21,590 --> 00:11:26,000
I'm not an orphan, and I didn't
grow up in Gray Terminal.

232
00:11:26,700 --> 00:11:29,370
The man who called out to me today was...

233
00:11:30,640 --> 00:11:31,970
my father.

234
00:11:33,770 --> 00:11:38,340
I was lying to you guys. I'm sorry.

235
00:11:38,340 --> 00:11:41,250
He said sorry. We gotta forgive him.

236
00:11:41,250 --> 00:11:43,980
It depends. This is kind of a shock for me.

237
00:11:44,650 --> 00:11:48,620
Why were you living there
if you're from a noble family?

238
00:11:51,590 --> 00:11:54,090
Let me tell you why I ran away...

239
00:11:59,300 --> 00:12:01,670
Listen, Sabo.

240
00:12:03,370 --> 00:12:07,970
You must acquire the intelligence
and knowledge befitting a noble

241
00:12:07,970 --> 00:12:11,840
and become a man worthy of
marrying into a royal family.

242
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:16,480
Doing so will secure our family's position,
and you will surely live happily ever after!

243
00:12:20,390 --> 00:12:23,220
Hello? Hello?!

244
00:12:23,220 --> 00:12:23,990
Blast it!

245
00:12:24,760 --> 00:12:27,690
By thunder, what a monumental loss!

246
00:12:30,060 --> 00:12:31,460
Dad!

247
00:12:32,140 --> 00:12:34,700
Look at this! I drew it for you!

248
00:12:42,010 --> 00:12:44,780
I'm exhausted from work, Sabo.

249
00:12:44,780 --> 00:12:48,380
If you have time to draw,
then you have time to study.

250
00:12:58,990 --> 00:13:00,600
Hey, you!

251
00:13:01,870 --> 00:13:03,900
I'm part of the royal family.

252
00:13:03,900 --> 00:13:08,030
That means I'm related to the king.
Give me a piggyback ride to my house!

253
00:13:14,640 --> 00:13:20,010
Stop, you insolent swine!
Who are you to ignore my royal decree?!

254
00:13:20,010 --> 00:13:22,380
What's the big idea?!

255
00:13:28,850 --> 00:13:33,490
You're just the son of some noble family!
I'll teach you a lesson!

256
00:13:34,930 --> 00:13:37,460
Stop it!

257
00:13:43,100 --> 00:13:47,340
It's unforgivable to harm
a child of the royal family!

258
00:13:47,340 --> 00:13:51,980
S-Sabo! Did you really get
in a fight with this royal boy?!

259
00:13:51,980 --> 00:13:54,650
Yeah, and I got hurt.

260
00:13:54,650 --> 00:13:57,950
He suddenly came at me with a knife, and–

261
00:14:03,460 --> 00:14:08,960
I'm so terribly sorry! He's not injured, is he?!

262
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:11,200
Please accept my sincerest apologies!

263
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:15,230
Let's have a doctor take a look at him!

264
00:14:15,230 --> 00:14:19,500
Can we please settle this matter peacefully?

265
00:14:20,570 --> 00:14:26,110
They love those who can maintain
their status and defend their property.

266
00:14:29,550 --> 00:14:30,550
Not me!

267
00:14:33,850 --> 00:14:37,720
If I can't marry a woman from
the royal family, I'm worthless!

268
00:14:37,720 --> 00:14:40,890
That's why I had to study
and learn about culture every day.

269
00:14:41,390 --> 00:14:45,330
They argued every day about how
I was falling behind in my studies.

270
00:14:46,160 --> 00:14:48,570
I had no place in that family!

271
00:14:49,400 --> 00:14:53,740
I'm sorry you're both orphans,
but even with parents, I was all by myself.

272
00:14:55,150 --> 00:15:00,150
I heard that you sneak out and
go somewhere now and then.

273
00:15:00,910 --> 00:15:06,220
I doubt you would, but don't ever go
anywhere near Gray Terminal!

274
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:11,420
We nobles are privileged to live in
High Town with the king and his family.

275
00:15:11,420 --> 00:15:17,060
Those residents below and we nobles above
live in two different worlds!

276
00:15:19,700 --> 00:15:23,800
The nobles don't think highly of Gray Terminal,

277
00:15:23,800 --> 00:15:26,700
but it's better than that stifling High Town,

278
00:15:26,700 --> 00:15:30,240
where they decide your
whole life decades in advance!

279
00:15:32,010 --> 00:15:33,650
I get the picture.

280
00:15:34,580 --> 00:15:36,710
Ace! Luffy!

281
00:15:37,450 --> 00:15:40,320
We gotta set out to sea someday!

282
00:15:40,750 --> 00:15:43,820
Let's get out of this country and live free!

283
00:15:43,820 --> 00:15:48,460
I wanna see the world out there
and write a book about it!

284
00:15:48,460 --> 00:15:51,230
Navigation is the one thing I do love to study!

285
00:15:51,230 --> 00:15:54,530
Let's get even stronger
and become pirates someday!

286
00:16:00,540 --> 00:16:04,240
That was my plan anyway!
You don't have to tell me twice!

287
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:10,080
When I'm a pirate, I'll beat up everyone
and become the biggest, baddest one of all!

288
00:16:10,650 --> 00:16:13,650
That's the only way I'll prove that I lived!

289
00:16:14,550 --> 00:16:20,590
It doesn't matter if the whole world
rejects or despises me,

290
00:16:20,590 --> 00:16:23,490
I'll become a great pirate and show them all!

291
00:16:24,330 --> 00:16:27,330
I won't run from anyone!
I won't lose to anyone!

292
00:16:27,330 --> 00:16:30,270
Whether I'm feared, or hated, or whatever,

293
00:16:30,270 --> 00:16:32,370
my name will be known all over!

294
00:16:34,010 --> 00:16:36,610
I got it! Alright then...!

295
00:16:39,380 --> 00:16:42,880
I'm gonna...!

296
00:16:45,520 --> 00:16:46,750
– Huh?!
– Huh?!

297
00:16:49,920 --> 00:16:53,260
Man... I was wondering what you would say...

298
00:16:56,060 --> 00:16:58,200
You're a riot, Luffy!

299
00:16:58,200 --> 00:17:01,400
I can't wait to see what future you is like!

300
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:05,640
Wait. We can all become pirates, but...

301
00:17:05,640 --> 00:17:09,240
isn't it a problem if we all wanna be captain?

302
00:17:10,170 --> 00:17:12,010
I wasn't expecting that...

303
00:17:12,010 --> 00:17:15,750
Sabo... I thought you'd be my ship's navigator.

304
00:17:15,750 --> 00:17:18,020
You guys can come aboard my ship!

305
00:17:18,020 --> 00:17:19,250
– No way!
– No way!

306
00:17:21,550 --> 00:17:24,720
Well, let's cross that bridge when we get there.

307
00:17:24,720 --> 00:17:28,030
Maybe we'll all set out on our own.

308
00:17:29,130 --> 00:17:31,230
Oh, did you steal that from Dadan?

309
00:17:32,660 --> 00:17:34,200
Did you guys know?

310
00:17:35,900 --> 00:17:39,000
We become brothers
when we exchange sake cups.

311
00:17:40,170 --> 00:17:42,610
Brothers? Really?!

312
00:17:42,610 --> 00:17:47,410
When we're pirates,
we might not be on the same ship,

313
00:17:47,410 --> 00:17:50,720
but we'll always be connected in brotherhood!

314
00:17:51,050 --> 00:17:54,490
No matter where we are or what we do,
this bond will never be broken.

315
00:17:57,690 --> 00:17:59,990
Starting today...

316
00:18:00,790 --> 00:18:02,060
we're brothers!

317
00:18:08,870 --> 00:18:10,800
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

318
00:19:54,210 --> 00:19:55,440
Give Sabo back!

319
00:19:55,440 --> 00:19:57,640
What do you mean "give him back"?

320
00:19:57,640 --> 00:19:59,520
Sabo is my son.

321
00:19:59,520 --> 00:20:03,780
Parents give life to their children,
so it's natural they do as they're told.

322
00:20:03,780 --> 00:20:07,890
How dare you two tempt Sabo to run away?!

323
00:20:07,890 --> 00:20:10,350
You wannabe thugs!

324
00:20:10,350 --> 00:20:12,660
Is it my money you're after?

325
00:20:12,660 --> 00:20:14,160
What'd you say?!

326
00:20:17,030 --> 00:20:20,970
You damn pirates need to be
careful when you hit these kids!

327
00:20:20,970 --> 00:20:23,770
You got that vermin's blood on me!

328
00:20:25,100 --> 00:20:25,640
Ace!

329
00:20:28,540 --> 00:20:32,010
Stop it! Nobody tempted me!

330
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:34,310
I ran away of my own free will!

331
00:20:34,310 --> 00:20:36,710
You stay out of this! Take him.

332
00:20:38,720 --> 00:20:41,090
I'll leave the rest up to you pirates.

333
00:20:41,090 --> 00:20:44,990
Of course, good sir.
You paid in advance, after all.

334
00:20:45,640 --> 00:20:51,260
We'll make sure these two
won't bother your boy again.

335
00:20:52,130 --> 00:20:57,240
Wait a minute, Bluejam!
Dad, that's enough! I understand!

336
00:20:58,040 --> 00:21:00,170
You understand what, exactly?

337
00:21:01,370 --> 00:21:02,740
Don't do it, Sabo!

338
00:21:04,380 --> 00:21:10,110
I'll do as you say.
I'll live as you want.

339
00:21:10,110 --> 00:21:14,820
So... I request that you don't hurt these two!

340
00:21:14,820 --> 00:21:17,120
I'm begging you.

341
00:21:17,120 --> 00:21:19,820
They're very dear to me;
they're my brothers.

342
00:21:20,960 --> 00:21:22,160
Sabo...

343
00:21:23,230 --> 00:21:26,730
Then go straight home.

344
00:21:26,730 --> 00:21:30,670
Enough playing pirate.
It's a waste of time.

345
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:34,810
Hey! Don't go!

346
00:21:34,810 --> 00:21:36,310
Be quiet!

347
00:21:36,310 --> 00:21:40,440
Sabo, run! Don't worry about us!

348
00:21:40,440 --> 00:21:43,310
You said you wanted to live free with us!

349
00:21:43,310 --> 00:21:45,820
Sabo, don't go!

350
00:21:45,820 --> 00:21:48,720
Is this how you want it to end?!

351
00:21:49,260 --> 00:21:50,320
Sabo!

352
00:21:53,490 --> 00:21:54,860
Sabo!

353
00:21:59,400 --> 00:22:01,970
Sabo!

354
00:22:08,070 --> 00:22:10,680
Captain! What should we do with these kids?

355
00:22:11,780 --> 00:22:13,650
Take them to our hideout.

356
00:22:13,650 --> 00:22:14,650
Yes, sir.

357
00:22:15,410 --> 00:22:17,680
Untie me, you jerk!

358
00:22:17,680 --> 00:22:20,690
I want a rematch! I'm not gonna lose this time!

359
00:22:20,690 --> 00:22:26,020
Nobles have it pretty good,
don't you think, brats?

360
00:22:26,020 --> 00:22:29,760
They look down on trash like us
and order everyone around.

361
00:22:29,760 --> 00:22:32,660
They sure do live the good life.

362
00:22:32,660 --> 00:22:35,230
It must be nice, right?

363
00:22:35,230 --> 00:22:37,470
What are you getting at?!

364
00:22:37,470 --> 00:22:41,810
Being a pirate is way better! Sabo said so!

365
00:22:41,810 --> 00:22:46,980
I can't help but feel bad for you kiddos.
Hey, go ahead and untie them.

366
00:22:46,980 --> 00:22:47,910
Yes, sir.

367
00:22:47,910 --> 00:22:53,920
Why do you think a kid from a noble family
escaped to a place like Gray Terminal?

368
00:22:55,120 --> 00:23:01,090
No doubt he did it to mock
the people here, just like all nobles do.

369
00:23:01,090 --> 00:23:04,660
I bet he looked down on you guys too.

370
00:23:04,660 --> 00:23:07,870
That's crazy! Sabo's not like that!

371
00:23:07,870 --> 00:23:10,370
He's right! We're brothers!

372
00:23:10,370 --> 00:23:13,400
Yeah? Alright, I'm sorry.

373
00:23:14,210 --> 00:23:18,910
But you won't be going near
that brat anymore, are you?

374
00:23:18,910 --> 00:23:23,750
If you try, I'd have to kill you both right here.

375
00:23:23,750 --> 00:23:27,590
If you care for him like a brother,
leaving him alone is for his own good.

376
00:23:29,090 --> 00:23:31,920
For Sabo's good?

377
00:23:31,920 --> 00:23:34,330
But Sabo hates High Town!

378
00:23:34,330 --> 00:23:39,430
If you really care about him,
you'll let him go.

379
00:23:39,430 --> 00:23:42,270
You'll understand when
you're older. By the way...

380
00:23:42,270 --> 00:23:47,200
I had an axe to grind with you about
what became of Porchemy...

381
00:23:47,200 --> 00:23:52,080
But we can forget about that.
I rather liked your show of strength.

382
00:23:52,080 --> 00:23:56,650
That's why I wanted to ask you something.
I think you might be interested.

383
00:23:56,650 --> 00:23:59,180
I'm short-handed now.

384
00:23:59,180 --> 00:24:03,150
Do you guys wanna do some work for me?

385
00:24:03,150 --> 00:24:08,160
Come on, it's a simple job.
No danger whatsoever.

386
00:24:08,160 --> 00:24:11,160
Right here's a map of Gray Terminal.

387
00:24:11,160 --> 00:24:15,370
All you have to do is carry packages
to the places marked on the map.

388
00:24:15,370 --> 00:24:16,630
You up for it?

389
00:24:16,630 --> 00:24:17,970
Fine.

390
00:24:19,270 --> 00:24:20,440
What's it pay?

391
00:24:25,210 --> 00:24:29,280
Ace, I don't like it when Sabo's not around.

392
00:24:29,280 --> 00:24:33,320
Live with it. I don't like it either.
I wanna rescue Sabo.

393
00:24:34,250 --> 00:24:38,620
But I don't know what's really best for him.

394
00:24:39,360 --> 00:24:42,430
Let's see how things play out.
He'll pull through!

395
00:24:42,430 --> 00:24:45,760
If he really hates it there,
he'll definitely come back.

396
00:24:46,520 --> 00:24:51,240
Let's make some money
for our pirate stash, just in case.

397
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:54,870
I can't say it. It's not Ace and Luffy's fault.

398
00:24:54,870 --> 00:24:58,040
Why can't you tell the truth?!

399
00:24:58,040 --> 00:25:03,250
Could it be...? They warned
you not to say anything?

400
00:25:03,250 --> 00:25:06,020
They're not like that!

401
00:25:06,020 --> 00:25:10,990
If you have a criminal record,
it will harm your family's standing.

402
00:25:10,990 --> 00:25:12,960
You won't be able to enter High Town.

403
00:25:12,960 --> 00:25:19,200
You were tempted by those two, having
no choice but to get involved in violence...

404
00:25:19,820 --> 00:25:21,100
weren't you, Sabo?

405
00:25:23,400 --> 00:25:25,100
Sabo.

406
00:25:25,100 --> 00:25:30,410
The fate of your friends in Gray Terminal
is in the hands of those pirates.

407
00:25:30,410 --> 00:25:32,940
All I need do is to give the order.

408
00:25:32,940 --> 00:25:37,980
If they're that important to you,
think about what you have to do.

409
00:25:40,820 --> 00:25:45,220
You're a smart boy.
Choose the right course of action.

410
00:25:46,090 --> 00:25:49,660
You promised that you wouldn't hurt them!

411
00:25:49,660 --> 00:25:52,300
That's why I came back here!

412
00:25:52,300 --> 00:25:56,330
A crime is a crime!
We did it of our own free will!

413
00:25:59,740 --> 00:26:01,570
Really now!

414
00:26:02,410 --> 00:26:06,140
It's a tragedy I have
such an addle-brained son!

415
00:26:07,110 --> 00:26:09,910
Can't you understand my dilemma?

416
00:26:09,280 --> 00:26:09,910
Oh...!

417
00:26:09,910 --> 00:26:12,620
It must be so hard.

418
00:26:13,350 --> 00:26:15,820
I'll handle the paperwork.

419
00:26:19,060 --> 00:26:21,960
Welcome back, sir.

420
00:26:21,960 --> 00:26:26,360
Okay, Sabo, let's go. It's been
a long while since you left.

421
00:26:26,360 --> 00:26:30,100
Oh, don't go in yet; you're filthy.

422
00:26:30,100 --> 00:26:32,740
Wash and disinfect your body in the yard first.

423
00:26:32,740 --> 00:26:34,870
Then you can take a bath.

424
00:26:34,870 --> 00:26:38,210
I'm glad that you're safe, Young Master.

425
00:26:38,210 --> 00:26:42,540
Oh, Sabo, you've returned!
Look how much you've grown.

426
00:26:44,010 --> 00:26:44,920
Mom.

427
00:26:44,920 --> 00:26:47,750
Now, Sterry, say "hi" to your older brother.

428
00:26:47,750 --> 00:26:50,350
It's a pleasure to meet you, Brother!

429
00:26:50,350 --> 00:26:52,820
My name is Sterry. I'm eight.

430
00:26:53,560 --> 00:26:54,790
Who's he?

431
00:26:56,290 --> 00:27:00,060
We adopted him. He's a smart
boy from a noble family.

432
00:27:00,060 --> 00:27:04,400
But due to certain circumstances,
his parents gave up on raising him.

433
00:27:04,400 --> 00:27:08,440
We took him in since he's full of promise.

434
00:27:08,440 --> 00:27:12,580
If you don't work out to be my successor–

435
00:27:13,810 --> 00:27:16,880
No, I've said too much.

436
00:27:16,880 --> 00:27:18,280
Go to bed now.

437
00:27:18,280 --> 00:27:20,560
Tomorrow, you renew your studies.

438
00:27:29,830 --> 00:27:32,500
Is this how you want it to end?!

439
00:27:35,530 --> 00:27:37,600
My dear older brother...

440
00:27:37,600 --> 00:27:40,200
I heard that you're pretty stupid.

441
00:27:40,870 --> 00:27:44,410
Mother and Father always
say so behind your back.

442
00:27:44,410 --> 00:27:49,250
But you sure have the devil's luck.
Tomorrow night, they're burning all the trash!

443
00:27:50,780 --> 00:27:53,620
If you had stayed in Gray Terminal...

444
00:27:54,790 --> 00:27:57,420
you would have died.

445
00:27:58,520 --> 00:28:05,000
Well, it would've been better for me
had their real son not come ba–

446
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:08,900
Wh-Wh-What are you doing?!
Wh-When Father hears abou–

447
00:28:08,900 --> 00:28:11,600
What you just said... What was that?!

448
00:28:11,600 --> 00:28:13,940
What's going on? Tell me everything!

449
00:28:13,940 --> 00:28:19,010
Th-There's gonna be a fire
in Gray Terminal tomorrow.

450
00:28:19,010 --> 00:28:20,080
A fire?!

451
00:28:20,080 --> 00:28:21,480
Yeah.

452
00:28:21,480 --> 00:28:24,750
You don't know about it
because you weren't here.

453
00:28:24,750 --> 00:28:27,380
But it was decided months ago.

454
00:28:27,990 --> 00:28:32,420
Did you know the World Government sent
a group of observers to survey the East Blue?

455
00:28:33,190 --> 00:28:37,260
They're due to arrive in Goa Kingdom
three days from now!

456
00:28:37,260 --> 00:28:43,370
And one of the world nobles—a Celestial Dragon
—is traveling with them, so everyone's panicking!

457
00:28:43,370 --> 00:28:48,570
The members of the royal family want
to avoid having him see our shame,

458
00:28:48,570 --> 00:28:52,540
so they decided to
burn down Gray Terminal.

459
00:28:52,540 --> 00:28:55,750
Then this country will be clean!

460
00:28:55,750 --> 00:29:00,880
What the hell are you talking about?!
They can't do that!!

461
00:29:00,880 --> 00:29:04,460
Just the sheer number of people living there...!

462
00:29:04,460 --> 00:29:06,990
This would destroy their home!

463
00:29:06,990 --> 00:29:07,730
Hands off!

464
00:29:08,460 --> 00:29:11,230
Did you hear a word I said?

465
00:29:13,100 --> 00:29:17,100
This country's shame will all burn to ash.

466
00:29:17,740 --> 00:29:19,940
Including the people...?

467
00:29:26,710 --> 00:29:27,710
H-Hey!

468
00:29:29,910 --> 00:29:31,350
Where are you going?

469
00:29:35,850 --> 00:29:37,520
What floor do you think we're on?

470
00:29:41,830 --> 00:29:44,090
I-It's not my fault...

471
00:29:44,500 --> 00:29:46,630
It's a lie! He must be lying!

472
00:29:46,630 --> 00:29:51,000
It's not like they can just
burn down an area that big!

473
00:29:55,470 --> 00:29:57,540
It's those guys from earlier...

474
00:29:59,010 --> 00:30:02,850
Are we ready for tomorrow?
There can't be any miscalculation.

475
00:30:02,850 --> 00:30:06,680
We're ready, but the pirates
are a wild card here.

476
00:30:06,680 --> 00:30:09,750
They have to burn the trash precisely.

477
00:30:09,750 --> 00:30:13,760
Bluejam's crew is setting
boxes of oil and explosives

478
00:30:13,760 --> 00:30:17,800
all over Gray Terminal in preparation
for the appointed time tomorrow.

479
00:30:18,760 --> 00:30:22,430
Bluejam has a hand in this?
Then it must be true!

480
00:30:22,430 --> 00:30:24,330
Even though it's crazy!

481
00:30:34,810 --> 00:30:37,510
I wonder how Sabo's doing...

482
00:30:37,510 --> 00:30:40,020
Shut up and go to sleep.

483
00:30:41,020 --> 00:30:44,290
We agreed to let go of Sabo for now.

484
00:30:44,300 --> 00:30:45,420
Okay.

485
00:30:46,490 --> 00:30:49,460
Maybe... he would be happier there.

486
00:30:54,300 --> 00:30:59,770
I'll uncover the truth about the fire
by seeing how the townsfolk are acting.

487
00:31:03,370 --> 00:31:05,210
Oh, good morning!

488
00:31:05,210 --> 00:31:06,480
And a good morning to you!

489
00:31:06,480 --> 00:31:08,650
Isn't it a lovely morning?

490
00:31:08,650 --> 00:31:09,910
Yes, it is.

491
00:31:09,910 --> 00:31:14,150
Oh, great! Everything seems normal!

492
00:31:14,150 --> 00:31:15,990
I'll need to see more in town.

493
00:31:18,520 --> 00:31:20,690
Today is quite windy.

494
00:31:20,690 --> 00:31:24,030
Indeed it is, Your Majesty.

495
00:31:24,030 --> 00:31:26,160
Such days beget accidents...

496
00:31:26,160 --> 00:31:29,330
especially the spreading of flames.

497
00:31:29,330 --> 00:31:33,040
Quite right, Your Majesty.

498
00:31:33,040 --> 00:31:36,170
Sabo... isn't here?!

499
00:31:36,170 --> 00:31:38,280
That ungrateful brat!

500
00:31:38,280 --> 00:31:42,580
He'd still rather play pirate
than attend to his studies?!

501
00:31:43,110 --> 00:31:44,980
Search all of High Town!

502
00:31:44,980 --> 00:31:47,990
He can't have left town so easily!

503
00:31:49,250 --> 00:31:51,050
Excuse me, mister.

504
00:31:51,050 --> 00:31:52,120
What is it, boy?

505
00:31:52,120 --> 00:31:56,360
Do you know that there'll be a fire
in Gray Terminal tonight?

506
00:31:56,360 --> 00:32:00,300
Of course, I know. What about it?

507
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:02,070
He knows?

508
00:32:02,070 --> 00:32:04,670
Which family are you from?

509
00:32:04,670 --> 00:32:07,540
So it's true!

510
00:32:09,110 --> 00:32:09,840
Boy, wait!

511
00:32:09,840 --> 00:32:13,310
What's going on here?
Everybody knows about it?

512
00:32:13,310 --> 00:32:16,510
They all know, and yet no one is bothered?!

513
00:32:16,510 --> 00:32:20,540
Doesn't anyone care about
the fire in Gray Terminal?!

514
00:32:24,050 --> 00:32:27,290
Oh... There you are, kiddos.

515
00:32:27,290 --> 00:32:29,560
Are there more boxes to carry today?

516
00:32:29,560 --> 00:32:32,860
Yeah, and I have a big task for you tonight.

517
00:32:32,860 --> 00:32:34,600
I'll tell you about it later.

518
00:32:34,600 --> 00:32:36,770
Yes, I know.

519
00:32:36,770 --> 00:32:41,910
Why does nobody here,
yourself included, look concerned?

520
00:32:41,910 --> 00:32:44,040
Why isn't anyone trying to prevent it?

521
00:32:46,080 --> 00:32:50,610
You sound like a kindhearted boy.

522
00:32:50,610 --> 00:32:53,280
But, listen carefully.

523
00:32:53,280 --> 00:32:56,620
We all have to keep quiet about the plan!

524
00:32:56,620 --> 00:33:01,460
What if someone outside
High Town finds out about it?

525
00:33:01,460 --> 00:33:05,930
We're special! If you're from a noble family...

526
00:33:07,500 --> 00:33:08,470
Hey, you!

527
00:33:09,700 --> 00:33:12,000
Ace! Luffy!

528
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:14,840
Something's wrong with this town!
Everybody's crazy!

529
00:33:15,740 --> 00:33:17,670
They know that people will die,

530
00:33:17,670 --> 00:33:20,510
but they're all unbothered and smiling!

531
00:33:21,210 --> 00:33:25,550
I don't wanna stay here!
I gotta tell them immediately!

532
00:33:27,550 --> 00:33:31,050
Why'd it have to be windy today, of all days?!

533
00:33:31,050 --> 00:33:33,360
There he is! Isn't that him?!

534
00:33:33,360 --> 00:33:35,590
No doubt about it! That's the runaway boy!

535
00:33:36,730 --> 00:33:38,360
Hey you, stop!

536
00:33:38,360 --> 00:33:44,030
Tonight, the people of this country are
planning to set fire to their national shame!

537
00:33:44,840 --> 00:33:48,410
Ace... Luffy... You need
to get out of Gray Terminal!

538
00:33:48,870 --> 00:33:52,440
Run! Ace! Luffy!

539
00:33:54,310 --> 00:33:55,710
Why would you do that?!

540
00:33:55,710 --> 00:34:01,450
You dumbass! Keep it down!
No one else can find out about this!

541
00:34:01,450 --> 00:34:04,190
This is serious! We gotta tell everybody!

542
00:34:04,190 --> 00:34:06,160
I knew he was a bad guy!

543
00:34:06,160 --> 00:34:08,330
I said to keep it down.

544
00:34:06,730 --> 00:34:09,890
What do you think you're doing, you jerks?!

545
00:34:08,330 --> 00:34:09,890
Restrain them, will ya?

546
00:34:09,890 --> 00:34:13,670
Hey! Let go, jerks! Let us go!

547
00:34:11,300 --> 00:34:13,660
I'm not the mastermind.

548
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:21,170
There were oil and explosives in the boxes
you guys were carrying the last two days.

549
00:34:21,170 --> 00:34:25,910
No one will escape the massive
fire that's about to happen.

550
00:34:25,910 --> 00:34:27,210
N-No...

551
00:34:27,210 --> 00:34:28,710
Are you nuts?

552
00:34:30,150 --> 00:34:33,320
Even punk kids like you two
are freaking out, huh?

553
00:34:34,080 --> 00:34:36,890
But now you know about the plan.

554
00:34:37,990 --> 00:34:41,860
We can't just let you go anymore.

555
00:34:41,860 --> 00:34:45,800
Before the fire starts,
I've got something I wanna ask.

556
00:34:46,630 --> 00:34:52,200
You boys wouldn't happen to have
a treasure trove somewhere, would you?

557
00:35:16,490 --> 00:35:20,160
Edge Town

558
00:35:21,260 --> 00:35:22,530
Shut up!

559
00:35:23,530 --> 00:35:26,140
H-Hey! Look at that!

560
00:35:30,070 --> 00:35:32,810
Something's wrong in Gray Terminal.

561
00:35:32,810 --> 00:35:34,380
It's on fire...?

562
00:35:39,550 --> 00:35:42,120
This is the best game I've ever played!

563
00:35:42,120 --> 00:35:45,920
B-B-Boss! Boss! You gotta see this!

564
00:35:46,220 --> 00:35:47,820
What're you screamin' about?

565
00:35:47,820 --> 00:35:49,990
Look at the sky in the north!

566
00:35:49,990 --> 00:35:50,990
Is that the town?!

567
00:35:50,990 --> 00:35:54,830
No, closer than that! Must be
Gray Terminal! It's on fire!

568
00:35:57,130 --> 00:35:59,900
What's going on? It's as big as a wildfire!

569
00:35:57,130 --> 00:35:59,900
Midtown

570
00:35:59,900 --> 00:36:03,470
Gray Terminal has never caught fire before!

571
00:36:05,010 --> 00:36:07,740
It's dangerous! Evacuate Edge Town!

572
00:36:07,740 --> 00:36:10,380
All residents must head to Midtown!

573
00:36:07,740 --> 00:36:10,380
Great Gate, Edge Town

574
00:36:10,860 --> 00:36:15,120
We're the military, so leave the
lifesaving and fire extinguishing to us!

575
00:36:18,690 --> 00:36:20,130
Everybody, wake up!

576
00:36:20,130 --> 00:36:21,830
We gotta get outta here!

577
00:36:24,390 --> 00:36:26,760
The fire is spreading all around!

578
00:36:26,760 --> 00:36:28,600
We can't stay here!

579
00:36:28,600 --> 00:36:31,870
It's no use! Give it up!
Leave your home behind and run!

580
00:36:35,010 --> 00:36:37,810
Oh no! The fire has
already reached the shore!

581
00:36:37,810 --> 00:36:39,740
And the forest entrance is ablaze!

582
00:36:40,280 --> 00:36:43,050
Where should we go,
dammit?! We're stranded!

583
00:36:46,850 --> 00:36:50,920
Burn it all down, men!

584
00:36:52,990 --> 00:36:55,290
Once the job's done...

585
00:36:55,290 --> 00:36:58,800
my long-cherished dream will come true!

586
00:36:59,900 --> 00:37:01,030
You're right.

587
00:37:01,030 --> 00:37:04,940
We don't give a damn
about the other people living here.

588
00:37:04,940 --> 00:37:11,110
While this place is pretty shabby,
it's not a bad hiding spot, Your Majesty.

589
00:37:11,110 --> 00:37:14,240
I'm aware of that, Bluejam.

590
00:37:14,240 --> 00:37:18,520
But when this is over,
you no longer need to hide.

591
00:37:18,520 --> 00:37:23,490
I will use my authority to make you all nobles.

592
00:37:24,820 --> 00:37:27,060
Will you really?!

593
00:37:27,890 --> 00:37:31,390
The king will give us all titles,

594
00:37:31,390 --> 00:37:35,400
and we'll live in High Town as privileged nobles!

595
00:37:42,340 --> 00:37:45,980
It seems we'd best get a move on.

596
00:37:45,980 --> 00:37:49,550
To the Great Gate! The military is waiting.

597
00:37:49,550 --> 00:37:52,250
Captain, we left the brats in the hideout...

598
00:37:52,250 --> 00:37:56,820
Forget 'em. They could've joined my crew
had they come clean about the treasure.

599
00:37:59,590 --> 00:38:02,560
Fools don't live long anyway.

600
00:38:05,360 --> 00:38:08,100
Hey, Captain! It's closed!

601
00:38:08,100 --> 00:38:12,740
Don't panic. They just don't want
other people to get away.

602
00:38:12,740 --> 00:38:16,140
The plan is for me to give them a sign,
then they'll open the gate.

603
00:38:17,110 --> 00:38:19,610
It's me, Bluejam. Open up.

604
00:38:23,210 --> 00:38:25,150
Hey! Do you hear me?!

605
00:38:28,590 --> 00:38:29,690
Is this...?

606
00:38:30,890 --> 00:38:33,260
Captain, don't tell me...

607
00:38:34,620 --> 00:38:40,060
Hey, you guys, what are
you doing?! Open the gate!

608
00:38:40,060 --> 00:38:44,070
You were supposed to let us
evacuate through here, right?!

609
00:38:44,070 --> 00:38:47,700
This wasn't the deal! You bastards!

610
00:38:47,700 --> 00:38:50,270
What about your promise, Your Majesty?!

611
00:38:50,270 --> 00:38:53,110
You said that you'd make us nobles–

612
00:38:54,880 --> 00:38:58,080
You set us up?! Your Majesty!

613
00:38:58,080 --> 00:39:00,620
Dammit!

614
00:39:01,320 --> 00:39:02,420
Did you hear?

615
00:39:02,420 --> 00:39:07,290
Bluejam, a pirate in the
Gray Terminal, started the fire.

616
00:39:07,290 --> 00:39:08,730
I thought so!

617
00:39:08,730 --> 00:39:11,030
No one else would do that.

618
00:39:11,030 --> 00:39:15,770
He did it to try to keep the observers
from the World Government away.

619
00:39:15,770 --> 00:39:17,630
How terrible!

620
00:39:21,540 --> 00:39:24,740
Hot! It's hot!

621
00:39:24,740 --> 00:39:25,980
Got it!

622
00:39:25,980 --> 00:39:28,450
Dammit! We got dragged into all this!

623
00:39:30,010 --> 00:39:32,680
We can't get away! I don't wanna die!

624
00:39:32,680 --> 00:39:34,620
Keep complaining, and I'll leave you!

625
00:39:35,390 --> 00:39:36,620
Not hot at all...

626
00:39:38,220 --> 00:39:40,490
Whoa, it's hot! Not...!

627
00:39:40,490 --> 00:39:42,630
The fire's everywhere!

628
00:39:42,630 --> 00:39:44,260
I can't breathe...

629
00:39:44,260 --> 00:39:45,730
Yes, I can!

630
00:39:45,730 --> 00:39:47,630
The air is hot!

631
00:39:47,630 --> 00:39:49,100
No, it's not.

632
00:39:49,100 --> 00:39:53,300
We're gonna be okay! I'm here with you!

633
00:39:53,300 --> 00:39:56,810
What are you doing?! You have to evacuate!

634
00:39:56,810 --> 00:39:58,380
Open the gate!

635
00:39:58,380 --> 00:39:59,910
What're you talking about?!

636
00:40:00,840 --> 00:40:03,280
Damn brat! Get him outta here!

637
00:40:05,150 --> 00:40:07,120
Ace! Luffy!

638
00:40:07,120 --> 00:40:08,150
Run!

639
00:40:12,790 --> 00:40:15,590
Stay away! Stay away from the lock!

640
00:40:15,990 --> 00:40:17,660
No!

641
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:19,960
Ace!

642
00:40:19,960 --> 00:40:21,700
Luffy!

643
00:40:30,340 --> 00:40:31,880
Be a good kid and evacuate!

644
00:40:31,880 --> 00:40:33,510
Don't give us any trouble!

645
00:40:37,410 --> 00:40:41,160
A-Ace... Luffy...

646
00:41:02,670 --> 00:41:05,140
What happened to you, boy?

647
00:41:09,880 --> 00:41:12,320
M-Mister...

648
00:41:15,390 --> 00:41:20,590
The royalty and the nobles...
caused the fire...!

649
00:41:23,490 --> 00:41:25,860
Please believe me...!

650
00:41:26,760 --> 00:41:32,640
This town smells worse than
Gray Terminal ever could.

651
00:41:32,640 --> 00:41:37,040
It's the people who are creating this stench!

652
00:41:38,640 --> 00:41:43,580
If I stay here... I'll never be free!

653
00:41:45,650 --> 00:41:49,890
I'm... ashamed of being born a noble!

654
00:41:50,580 --> 00:41:55,690
Look what you've made this boy say, Goa!

655
00:41:57,390 --> 00:42:01,740
I know how you feel.
I was born in this country, too.

656
00:42:02,570 --> 00:42:08,540
And yet, I still lack the power
to change this country.

657
00:42:08,540 --> 00:42:12,810
Mister, you're actually listening to me?

658
00:42:12,810 --> 00:42:15,150
Yes, and I'll never forget.
